### Variants

[
  Datatype variants
  Funcon   variant
  Funcon   variant-id
  Funcon   variant-value
]

Meta-variables
  T <: values

Datatype
  variants(T) ::= variant(_:ids, _:values)
/*
  A value of type `variants(T)` is a pair formed from an identifier and 
  a value of type `T`.
*/

Funcon
  variant-id(V:variants(T)) : =>ids
Rule
  variant-id(variant(I:ids, V:T)) ~> I

Funcon
  variant-value(V:variants(T)) : =>T
Rule
  variant-value(variant(I:ids, V:T)) ~> V
